{{nihongo|'''Nemuro'''|根室市|Nemuro-shi|[[Ainu language|Ainu]]: ''Ni mu oro''}} is a [[cities of Japan|city]] and [[seaports of Japan|port]] located in [[Nemuro Subprefecture|Nemuro]], [[Hokkaidō]].  It is the capital city of Nemuro Subprefecture. Much of the city lies on the [[Nemuro Peninsula]]. 

As of [[2008]], the city has an estimated [[population]] of 30,560 and the [[population density|density]] of 62.53 persons per [[square kilometer|km²]]. The total area is 512.64 km².

The city was founded on [[August 1]], [[1957]].

